sec.p:
The condition sets during the friction test are summarized as follows:


pin (8 × 8 mm2), plane (20 × 10 mm2), 3 mm thick (Figure 1);

normal applied load: Fn = 15.80 N;

frequency: 0.33 Hz (10 cycles/min);

average speed: 3.33 mm/s;

sliding distance: D = 5 mm;

contact area: S = 64 mm2;

anti-parallel orientation of fibers (Figure 1).
After the friction tests, dielectric measurements were carried out after 50 cycles on the plane in the friction zone (FZ) and outside the friction zone (NFZ) (Figure 1).
Figure 1.
(a) Anti-parallel orientation of fibers compared to the contact plane and the sliding displacement D. (b) Schematic representation of the friction track (FZ) and of the non-friction zone (NFZ) on the plane.
